ENERGY STAR

ENERGY STAR certifies electronics and appliances based on energy efficiency specifications set by the US EPA. The ENERGY STAR programme is administered by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA). EPA sets energy efficiency specifications for manufactures to earn the ENERGY STAR label for their products.
